---
// src/pages/privacy.astro
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/layout/Navbar';
import Footer from '../components/layout/Footer';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | JaldiDocs"
  description="JaldiDocs privacy policy. All file processing happens in your browser. We do not upload, store or access your files. Read our complete privacy policy."
  canonical="/privacy"
>
  <Navbar client:load />

  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-14">
    <div class="mb-10">
      <nav class="flex items-center gap-1.5 text-xs text-gray-400 mb-6">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-gray-600 transition-colors">Home</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <span class="text-gray-700 font-medium">Privacy Policy</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-gray-900 tracking-tight">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mt-2">Last updated: January 2025</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-emerald-50 border border-emerald-200 rounded-2xl px-6 py-5 mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-emerald-900 mb-2">The short version</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-emerald-800 leading-relaxed">
        JaldiDocs processes all your files entirely inside your browser. Your photos, PDFs, and documents
        are <strong>never uploaded to any server</strong>. We do not see, store, or have access to your files.
        Invoice and rent receipt drafts are saved only in your own browser's localStorage if you choose to
        save them, and never sent to us.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-tool space-y-8">
      <section>
        <h2>1. File Processing</h2>
        <p>
          All file operations on JaldiDocs â€” including image resizing, image compression, PDF merging,
          PDF compression, passport photo generation, invoice creation, and rent receipt generation â€” are
          performed entirely within your web browser using browser APIs (Canvas API, pdf-lib, jsPDF).
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Your files are not uploaded to any server.</strong> We do not have infrastructure to
          receive or store user files. When you close the browser tab, any files loaded into the tool are
          removed from your browser's memory.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>2. Locally Saved Data</h2>
        <p>
          Some tools (Invoice Maker, Rent Receipt Generator) offer a "Save Draft" feature. When you use
          this feature, the data (your business name, invoice items, rent details, etc.) is saved to your
          browser's <code>localStorage</code>. This data:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Is stored only on your device, in your browser</li>
          <li>Is never sent to JaldiDocs servers or any third party</li>
          <li>Can be cleared at any time using the "Clear" button in the tool, or by clearing your browser's localStorage/site data</li>
          <li>Is lost if you clear your browser data or use a different browser or device</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>3. Personal Data We Do Not Collect</h2>
        <p>In this current free MVP version of JaldiDocs, we do not collect:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Name, email address, or any contact details (no signup required)</li>
          <li>User files or documents</li>
          <li>Aadhaar numbers, PAN numbers, or any government ID information</li>
          <li>Financial information</li>
          <li>Location data</li>
          <li>Cookies (beyond what is technically set by the browser for the session)</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>4. Analytics and Advertising</h2>
        <p>
          The current MVP version of JaldiDocs does not include any third-party analytics or advertising
          scripts. In the future, we may add:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Privacy-respecting analytics (e.g. page views, tool usage counts â€” no personal data)</li>
          <li>Google AdSense or similar advertising, which may use cookies for ad personalisation</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          If and when such services are added, this Privacy Policy will be updated to reflect the change,
          and where required by law, consent will be sought.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>
          JaldiDocs is hosted on Cloudflare Pages. Cloudflare may collect standard server access logs
          (IP addresses, request paths, timestamps) as part of their infrastructure. Please refer to
          Cloudflare's privacy policy at cloudflare.com/privacypolicy for details on their data practices.
        </p>
        <p>
          Google Fonts are loaded from Google's CDN. Google may log basic request information. See Google's
          privacy policy at policies.google.com/privacy for details.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>6. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          JaldiDocs tools are general-purpose document utilities. We do not knowingly collect any information
          from users under the age of 13. The tools do not require any personal data input to function.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>7. Data Security</h2>
        <p>
          Since all file processing happens in your browser and we do not receive your files, the primary
          data security responsibility is your device's own browser security. Keep your browser updated
          and use trusted devices when working with sensitive documents.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy as the product evolves. If material changes are made, we will
          update the "Last updated" date at the top of this page. Continued use of the site after changes
          constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>9. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at
          <a href="mailto:supportjaldidocs@gmail.com" class="text-accent hover:underline">supportjaldidocs@gmail.com</a>.
          (Replace this email with your actual contact address before going live.)
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer client:load />
</BaseLayout>

